# Tunify project standards (mandatory)

For every change in this repository, comply with the **authoritative** docs at the repo root:

- @DESIGN.md — Spotify-inspired design system (dark surfaces, functional green `#1ed760`, pills/circles, typography, shadows, spacing).
- @RULES.md — Flutter architecture and quality (clean architecture, feature folders, Riverpod, no business logic in UI, repositories/DTOs, centralized theme, error handling, performance).

## How to apply them

1. **UI / theming**: Use centralized theme tokens and spacing; do not scatter hex values or one-off styles when the design system already defines the pattern. Match pill geometry, weights, and elevation from DESIGN.md.
2. **Structure & logic**: Follow RULES.md — presentation / domain / data separation, feature-based layout under `lib/features/`, immutable state, no raw API models in widgets.
3. **Conflicts**: If anything disagrees with DESIGN.md or RULES.md, **those two files win**.

When touching visuals or `lib/`, re-read the relevant sections of DESIGN.md and RULES.md if needed before implementing.
